<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="208" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d208">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 857.857/102</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SWG1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-22">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 22, 1917</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 5.30 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1948. Consul at La Rochelle reports Norwegian steamer <hi rend="italic">Girda</hi> bound from Glasgow to La Palice, general cargo, sunk
                            without warning by submarine By gunfire and bombs on 13th instant, about
                            12 miles from Chassiron Light, He d’Oléron. Two Americans on board,
                                <persName>Bryson Georges</persName> and <persName>Lloyd
                                Cain</persName>, one of whom slightly injured in foot; Consul states
                            Americans departed for Marseilles be <pb facs="0355" n="183" xml:id="pg_183"/> fore he was able to take depositions. I have
                            telegraphed Consul General at Marseilles to endeavor to find these men
                            and obtain depositions and have instructed Consul at [<hi rend="italic">near?</hi>] La Palice to obtain, if possible, needed additional
                            information.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_SWG1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sharp</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>